==English==

===Interjection===
'''[[has]]/[[have]]''' ''one'''''?'''

# ''[[request|Request]] for [[confirmation]] that converts a negative present perfect tense sentence into a [[question]]. Expects [[agreement]] in a "no" answer.''
#:''We haven't eaten dinner yet, '''have we'''?''
#:''Your wife hasn't been reading that nonsense, '''has she'''?''
#:''I'd bet Peter hasn't written his homework yet, '''has he'''?''

====Usage notes====
As a tag, always used with an object pronoun substituting for the subject. Number distinguishes between ''has'' and ''have''.

This construction does not apply to present tense sentences with ''has'' or ''have'', or their negations, as a verb. In those cases, use "[[does one?]]" instead.

